CalculateField EFH_Mapper_Data DATACAVEATS "This data layer uses habitat and coastline data to define the extents of EFH in near-shore areas. Habitat and coastline data can be subject to georeferencing and data resolution errors. The upstream extents of EFH portrayed by this layer may not reflect the true range of the species. The habitat data used to define near-shore areas of EFH may be subject to data aggregation errors including the loss of 'no data' information, and may no longer represent current ground conditions. This data layer should be used as an indication that a habitat type may exist at or near a specific location but should not be relied upon to provide accurate presence or absence information with a high degree of spatial precision." VB #

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset dipicts the boundary of essential fish habitat for managed species in the EFH Mapper. Last update as of December 1, 2020.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Essential Fish Habitat are those areas that have been identified and described by species and lifestage. Fish require healthy surroundings to survive and reproduce. Essential fish haitat includes all types of aquatic habitat - wetlands, coral reefs, sea-grasses, rivers - where fish spawn, breed, feed, or growh to maturity. EFH Mapper Data is a combination of three existing data layers: Essential Fish Habitat (EFH), Habitat Areas of Particular Concern (HAPC) and EFH Areas Protected from Fishing (EFHA).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: NOAA Fisheries / Office of Habitat Conservation / Habitat Protection Division
